<subSubSection id="C34F12C8FFEDFA58D9FF3A7BFDF66E51" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BEA4143FFEDFA58D9FF3A7BFE806F6B" blockId="30.[189,310,592,618]" box="[189,310,592,618]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<heading id="D0A2F62FFFEDFA58D9FF3A7BFE806F6B" bold="true" box="[189,310,592,618]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B9219D51FFEDFA58D9FF3A7BFE806F6B" bold="true" box="[189,310,592,618]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEA4143FFEDFA58D9FF3AABFDF66E51" blockId="30.[189,1399,639,848]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
Differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C553AC0FFEDFA58D8143AABFCB06F9B" authority="Tebbitt (Tebbit 2005)" authorityName="Tebbitt (Tebbitt" authorityYear="2005" box="[342,774,639,666]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scottii">
<emphasis id="B9219D51FFEDFA58D8143AABFDB16F98" box="[342,519,640,665]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Begonia scottii</emphasis>
Tebbitt (Tebbit 2005)
</taxonomicName>
in bearing fruit in clusters of 10–15 (not 2 or 4), with the fruit being fleshier and rounder, with ridges rather than small wings. The infructescence in terms of fruit number and shape is more similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C553AC0FFEDFA58DA783AE2FB5A6FE3" authority="Blume (Blume 1827)" authorityName="Blume (Blume" authorityYear="1827" box="[826,1260,712,738]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="multangula">
<emphasis id="B9219D51FFEDFA58DA783AE2FC526FE3" box="[826,996,712,738]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">B. multangula</emphasis>
Blume (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC43CB2FFEDFA58DD0C3AE3FB526FE3" author="Blume C. L." box="[1102,1252,712,738]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" refId="ref17665" refString="Blume C. L. 1827. Enumeratio Plantarum Javae et insularum adjacentium minus cognitarum vel novarum ex herbariis Reinwardtii, Kuhlii, Hasseltii et Blumii curavit Carol. Ludov. Blume. Apud J. W. van Leeuwen, Lugduni Batavorum [Leiden]. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 44901" type="book" year="1827">Blume 1827</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, which has lobed leaves that are either subglabrous or have white hairs (not pink), and apical (not basal) more lax infructesences. The flowers have pink centres to the tepals (uniform white in 
<taxonomicName id="4C553AC0FFEDFA58DD113B3AFB0A6E2B" authorityName="Tebbitt (Tebbitt" authorityYear="2005" box="[1107,1212,785,810]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scottii">
<emphasis id="B9219D51FFEDFA58DD113B3AFB0A6E2B" box="[1107,1212,785,810]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">B. scottii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the leaves have deep pink hairs (not white).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34F12C8FFEDFA58D9FF3B5CFEA06EE4" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BEA4143FFEDFA58D9FF3B5CFEF26E90" blockId="30.[189,324,887,913]" box="[189,324,887,913]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<heading id="D0A2F62FFFEDFA58D9FF3B5CFEF26E90" bold="true" box="[189,324,887,913]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B9219D51FFEDFA58D9FF3B5CFEF26E90" bold="true" box="[189,324,887,913]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEA4143FFEDFA58D9FF3B8CFEA06EE4" blockId="30.[189,1398,935,998]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
The epithet refers to the previous confusion of this species with 
<taxonomicName id="4C553AC0FFEDFA58DA9F3B83FEB96EE7" authority="(Hughes &amp; Girmansyah 2011 b)" baseAuthorityName="Hughes &amp; Girmansyah" baseAuthorityYear="2011" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scottii">
<emphasis id="B9219D51FFEDFA58DA9F3B83FBFC6EC0" box="[989,1098,936,961]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">B. scottii</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC43CB2FFEDFA58DD1F3B8CFEB16EE7" author="Hughes M. &amp; Girmansyah D." pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="83 - 96" refId="ref18049" refString="Hughes M. &amp; Girmansyah D. 2011 b. Searching for Sumatran Begonia described by William Jack: following in the footsteps of a 19 th century Scottish botanist. Gardens' Bulletin Singapore 63 (1 &amp; 2): 83 - 96." type="journal article" year="2011">Hughes &amp; Girmansyah 2011b</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
